<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,151,588]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,151,177]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Piskunov" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[330,473,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolella">
<emphasis box="[330,473,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. lineolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from S Ural. However, because it was considered a problematic species according to the criteria of the catalogue of European 
<taxonomicName authority="(Karsholt et al. 1996)" baseAuthorityName="Karsholt" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[898,1309,189,215]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">
Lepidoptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Karsholt" box="[1058,1301,189,215]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Karsholt" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="310 - 312" refId="ref41150" refString="Karsholt, O., Riedl, T., Huemer, P. &amp; Povolny, D. (1996) Gelechiidae. In: Karsholt, O. &amp; Razowski, J. (eds): The Lepidoptera of Europe. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 103 - 122 &amp; 310 - 312." type="book chapter" year="1996">
Karsholt 
<emphasis box="[1171,1224,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
it was not mentioned in that work. Externally 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Piskunov" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[596,745,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolella">
<emphasis box="[596,745,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. lineolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the closely related 
<taxonomicName authority="Povolny, 1975" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Chionodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis box="[1274,1435,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. mongolica</emphasis>
Povolný, 1975
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a characteristic dark, distinct longitudinal basal streak in the forewing, which is missing in 
<emphasis box="[394,528,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1975" box="[394,523,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Chionodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">mongolica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and by the smaller size of the adult (
<quantity box="[977,1110,301,327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11–15 mm</quantity>
; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1975" box="[1155,1281,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Chionodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis box="[1155,1281,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<quantity box="[1289,1423,301,327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19 mm</quantity>
). There are also differences in the male genitalia: in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Piskunov" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[743,883,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolella">
<emphasis box="[743,883,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. lineolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the valva is more slender and gradually curved from base to tip, and the aedeagus is distinctly shorter; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1975" box="[835,989,376,401]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Chionodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis box="[835,989,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the valva is medially slightly broader and more strongly bent than in the other parts, and a narrow distal part of the aedeagus is longer. Recently described 
<taxonomicName authority="Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya, 2003" authorityName="Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2003" box="[270,743,450,476]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radicalis">
<emphasis box="[270,403,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. radicalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya" box="[410,743,450,476]" firstAuthor="Falkovitsh" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="113 - 147" refId="ref40588" refString="Falkovitsh, M. I. &amp; Bidzilya, O. V. (2003) Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera) reared from the larvae collected in Kyzylkum Desert, with description of new species. Proceedings of the Zoological Museum of Kiev Taras Shevchenko National University, 1, 113 - 147. [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2003">Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also has a longitudinal basal streak in the forewing, but the adult is larger (
<quantity box="[332,464,488,514]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="16.0">16–19 mm</quantity>
) and paler, and in the male genitalia the valva and the aedeagus are more slender than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Piskunov" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[314,457,525,550]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolella">
<emphasis box="[314,457,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. lineolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bidzilya pers. comm.; 
<bibRefCitation author="Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya" box="[746,1084,525,551]" firstAuthor="Falkovitsh" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="113 - 147" refId="ref40588" refString="Falkovitsh, M. I. &amp; Bidzilya, O. V. (2003) Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera) reared from the larvae collected in Kyzylkum Desert, with description of new species. Proceedings of the Zoological Museum of Kiev Taras Shevchenko National University, 1, 113 - 147. [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2003">Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya 2003</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Falkovitsh &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2003" box="[1105,1241,525,550]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Stomopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radicalis">
<emphasis box="[1105,1241,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">S. radicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reared from 
<taxonomicName box="[215,435,562,587]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turanica">
<emphasis box="[215,435,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Artemisia turanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
